==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[pæþ]], from West Germanic ''*paþa-'', of uncertain origin, but perhaps an early borrowing from an Iranian language (Avestan ''pɑntɑ'' (nominative), ''pɑθɑ'' (genitive) way, Old Persian ''pɑthi-''), in which case it would be derived from the same [[Indo-European]] root as English [[find]]).  Cognate with Dutch [[pad#Dutch|pad]], German [[Pfad]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/pæθ/}}
*{{audio|en-us-path.ogg|Audio (US)}}
